{"name":"Shifter","description":"A jQuery plugin for simple slide-out mobile navigation. ","version":"3.1.2","demo":"http:\/\/formstone.it\/components\/Shifter\/demo\/index.html","repository":"https:\/\/github.com\/Formstone\/Shifter","documentation":{"options":[{"name":"maxWidth","type":"string","default":"'980px'","description":"Width at which to auto-disable plugin"}],"methods":[{"name":"close","description":"Closes navigation if open","example":"$.shifter(\"close\");"},{"name":"enable","description":"Enables navigation system","example":"$.shifter(\"enable\");"},{"name":"destroy","description":"Removes instance of plugin","example":"$.shifter(\"destroy\");"},{"name":"disable","description":"Disables navigation system","example":"$.shifter(\"disable\");"},{"name":"open","description":"Opens navigation if closed","example":"$.shifter(\"open\");"},{"name":"init","description":"Initializes plugin","params":[{"name":"opts","type":"object","description":"Initialization options"}],"private":true},{"name":"onRespond","description":"Handles media query match change","private":true},{"name":"onClick","description":"Determines proper click \/ touch action","params":[{"name":"e","type":"object","description":"Event data"}],"private":true},{"name":"resetTouch","description":"Resets touch state","private":true},{"name":"classify","description":"Create class selector from text","params":[{"name":"text","type":"string","description":"Text to convert"}],"return":{"type":"string","description":"New class name"},"private":true}]},"files":{"js":["jquery.fs.shifter.js"],"css":["jquery.fs.shifter.css"]},"extra":"","demo_resources":"","demo_content":"<!--[DEMO:START-CONTENT]-->\n\n\t\t\t\t\t<!-- Basic -->\n\t\t\t\t\t<h2>Basic<\/h2>\n\t\t\t\t\t<p>Shifter works by checking for target elements in the DOM and binding events to them. This allows you to markup and style pages anyway you'd like, but at a minimum you need three specifically classed elements (including the <code>body<\/code> tag):<\/p>\n\n\t\t\t\t\t<pre class=\"example\"><code class=\"language-javascript\">$.shifter();<\/code><\/pre>\n\t\t\t\t\t<pre class=\"example\"><code class=\"language-markup\">&lt;body class=\"shifter\"&gt;\n\t&lt;div class=\"shifter-page\"&gt;\n\t\t&lt;span class=\"shifter-handle\"&gt;Menu&lt;\/span&gt;\n\t\t&lt;!-- Page Content --&gt;\n\t&lt;\/div&gt;\n\t&lt;nav class=\"shifter-navigation\"&gt;\n\t\t&lt;!-- Navigation --&gt;\n\t&lt;\/nav&gt;\n&lt;\/body&gt;<\/code><\/pre>\n\n\t\t\t\t\t<!--\n\t\t\t\t\t<h5>Demo<\/h5>\n\t\t\t\t\t<p>Check out the handle at the top-right of this page!<\/p>\n\t\t\t\t\t-->\n\n\t\t\t\t\t<!-- Breakpoint -->\n\t\t\t\t\t<h2>Breakpoint<\/h2>\n\t\t\t\t\t<p>By default, Shifter will enable itself on screens smaller then 980 pixels wide. You can specify a different width by setting the <code>maxWidth<\/code> option on initialization.<\/p>\n\n\t\t\t\t\t<pre class=\"example\"><code class=\"language-javascript\">$.shifter({\n\tmaxWidth: Infinity\n});<\/code><\/pre>\n\n\t\t\t\t\t<h5>Demo<\/h5>\n\t\t\t\t\t<p>Click or tap the handle at the top-right of this page!<\/p>\n\t\t\t\t\t<br>\n\n\t\t\t\t\t<!-- IE -->\n\t\t\t\t\t<h2>IE Support<\/h2>\n\t\t\t\t\t<p>When supporting IE you will need to include a <a href=\"https:\/\/gist.github.com\/benplum\/8045366\" target=\"_blank\">HTML5 enabler<\/a> and matchMedia polyfill (<a href=\"https:\/\/gist.github.com\/benplum\/8045336\" target=\"_blank\">IE 8<\/a>, <a href=\"https:\/\/gist.github.com\/benplum\/8045327\" target=\"_blank\">IE 9<\/a>).<\/p>\n\n\t\t\t\t\t"}